# analyze-account — read-only mailbox analysis

Analyse the engine mailbox of a **configured account of THIS project** and report
what's there and what needs attention. **ZERO side effects**: use only the
read-only verbs below — NEVER `draft-reply` / `chat` / `campaign send-draft` /
`settings.update` / memory writes / commits.

The argument is the account **name** (from `cs accounts`, e.g. `mario`). If none
was given, run `cs accounts`, show the options, and ask which (or analyse the
default). **Stay within THIS project** — `cs accounts` only lists this project's
accounts; never try to reach another project's mailbox.

All commands run from the repo root: `.venv/bin/python -m cs --account <name> <verb>`.

## 1. Resolve + verify the session (silently)

```bash
.venv/bin/python -m cs accounts
.venv/bin/python -m cs --account <name> whoami
```

Expect `signed_in: true` and the expected email. If it fails (daemon down, token
mint failure, wrong identity), **STOP** and report the one-line reason — do not guess.

## 2. Read the state (read-only)

- Open engine tasks:
  ```bash
  .venv/bin/python -m cs --account <name> tasks
  ```
- What still seems unanswered (the engine's processed view — memory + tasks +
  handled-state, not a raw thread re-read):
  ```bash
  .venv/bin/python -m cs --account <name> ask "Elenca la posta degli ultimi 7 giorni che sembra ancora senza risposta umana: per ciascuna mittente e oggetto. Solo elenco, niente bozze."
  ```
- Recent inbox threads (returns `{"threads":[…]}` — summaries):
  ```bash
  .venv/bin/python -m cs --account <name> rpc emails.search '{"query":"newer_than:14d","folder":"inbox","limit":50}'
  ```
- For any thread worth detail, read the **bodies** (returns `{"emails":[…]}`):
  ```bash
  .venv/bin/python -m cs --account <name> rpc emails.list_by_thread '{"thread_id":"<id>"}'
  ```
- Optional, per contact: `.venv/bin/python -m cs --account <name> dossier <email>`

## 3. Report (Italian, founder register)

Compact and skimmable: cosa è arrivato di rilevante, cosa è ancora aperto / da
gestire, eventuali urgenze o cose da non perdere. **NIENTE bozze, NIENTE invii** —
questa è solo analisi. Se poi vuoi agire su qualcosa è un passo separato ed
esplicito; l'invio resta comunque fuori da questo comando.
